ify a working state of Drupal before and after any code changes, or as a means for developers to write and execute tests for their modules. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@simpletest\">Testing module</a>.','','none'),(6472,NULL,'default','Running tests','','none'),(6473,NULL,'default','Visit the <a href=\"@admin-simpletest\">Testing page</a> to display a list of available tests. For comprehensive testing, select <em>all</em> tests, or individually select tests for more targeted testing. Note that it might take several minutes for all tests to complete. For more information on creating and modifying your own tests, see the <a href=\"@simpletest-api\">Testing API Documentation</a> in the Drupal handbook.','','none'),(6474,NULL,'default','After the tests run, a message will be displayed next to each test group indicating whether tests within it passed, failed, or had exceptions. A pass means that the test returned the expected results, while fail means that it did not. An exception normally indicates an error outside of the test, such as a PHP warning or notice. If there were failures or exceptions, the results will be expanded to show details, and the tests that had failures or exceptions will be indicated in red or pink rows. You can then use these results to refine your code and tests, until all tests pass.','','none'),(6475,NULL,'default','Administer tests','','none'),(6476,NULL,'default','The test run finished in @elapsed.','','none'),(6477,NULL,'default','Use the <em>Clean environment</em> button to clean-up temporary files and tables.','','none'),(6478,NULL,'default','The testing framework requires the PHP <a href=\"@open_basedir-url\">open_basedir</a> restriction to be disabled. Check your webserver configuration or contact your web host.','','none'),(6479,NULL,'default','The testing framework could not be installed because the PHP <a href=\"@curl_url\">cURL</a> library is not available.','','none'),(6480,NULL,'default','The testing framework could not be installed because the PHP <a href=\"@hash_url\">hash</a> extension is disabled.','','none'),(6481,NULL,'default','PHP open_basedir restriction','','none'),(6482,NULL,'default','unblock IP address','','none'),(6483,NULL,'default','block IP address','','none'),(6484,NULL,'default','The Statistics module shows you how often a given page is viewed, who viewed it, the previous page the user visited (referrer URL), and when it was viewed. These statistics are useful in determining how users are visiting and navigating your site. For more information, see the online handbook entry for the <a href=\"@statistics\">Statistics module</a>.','','none'),(6485,NULL,'default','Managing logs','','none'),(6486,NULL,'default','To enable collection of statistics, the <em>Enable access log</em> checkbox on the <a href=\"@statistics-settings\">Statistics settings page</a> must be checked. The <em>Discard access logs older than</em> setting on the settings page specifies the length of time entries are kept in the log before they are deleted. This setting requires a correctly configured <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a> to run.','','none'),(6487,NULL,'default','Viewing site usage','','none'),(6488,NULL,'default','The Statistics module can help you break down details about your users and how they are using the site. The module offers four reports:','','none'),(6489,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@recent-hits\">Recent hits</a> displays information about the latest activity on your site, including the URL and title of the page that was accessed, the user name (if available) and the IP address of the viewer.','','none'),(6490,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@top-referrers\">Top referrers</a> displays where visitors came from (referrer URL).','','none'),(6491,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@top-pages\">Top pages</a> displays a list of pages ordered by how often they were viewed.','','none'),(6492,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@top-visitors\">Top visitors</a> shows you the most active visitors for your site and allows you to ban abusive visitors.','','none'),(6493,NULL,'default','Displaying popular content','','none'),(6494,NULL,'default','The module includes a <em>Popular content</em> block that displays the most viewed pages today and for all time, and the last content viewed. To use the block, enable <em>Count content views</em> on the <a href=\"@statistics-settings\">statistics settings page</a>, and then you can enable and configure the block on the <a href=\"@blocks\">blocks administration page</a>.','','none'),(6495,NULL,'default','Page view counter','','none'),(6496,NULL,'default','The Statistics module includes a counter for each page that increases whenever the page is viewed. To use the counter, enable <em>Count content views</em> on the <a href=\"@statistics-settings\">statistics settings page</a>, and set the necessary <a href=\"@permissions\">permissions</a> (<em>View content hits</em>) so that the counter is visible to the users.','','none'),(6497,NULL,'default','Administer statistics','','none'),(6498,NULL,'default','View content access statistics','','none'),(6499,NULL,'default','View content hits','','none'),(6500,NULL,'default','Control details about what and how your site logs access statistics.','','none'),(6501,NULL,'default','The Syslog module logs events by sending messages to the logging facility of your web server\'s operating system. Syslog is an operating system administrative logging tool that provides valuable information for use in system management and security auditing. Most suited to medium and large sites, Syslog provides filtering tools that allow messages to be routed by type and severity. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\'@syslog\'>Syslog module</a> and PHP\'s <a href=\'@php_openlog\'>openlog</a> and <a href=\'@php_syslog\'>syslog</a> functions.','','none'),(6502,NULL,'default','Logging for UNIX, Linux, and Mac OS X','','none'),(6503,NULL,'default','On UNIX, Linux, and Mac OS X, the file <em>/etc/syslog.conf</em> defines the routing configuration. Messages can be flagged with the codes <code>LOG_LOCAL0</code> through <code>LOG_LOCAL7</code>. For information on Syslog facilities, severity levels, and how to set up <em>syslog.conf</em>, see the <em>syslog.conf</em> manual page on your command line.','','none'),(6504,NULL,'default','Logging for Microsoft Windows','','none'),(6505,NULL,'default','On Microsoft Windows, messages are always sent to the Event Log using the code <code>LOG_USER</code>.','','none'),(6506,NULL,'default','Syslog facility','','none'),(6507,NULL,'default','Depending on the system configuration, Syslog and other logging tools use this code to identify or filter messages from within the entire system log.','','none'),(6508,NULL,'default','The image %file could not be rotated because the imagerotate() function is not available in this PHP installation.','','none'),(6509,NULL,'default','The image %file could not be desaturated because the imagefilter() function is not available in this PHP installation.','','none'),(6510,NULL,'default','Screenshot for !theme theme','','7.57-dev'),(6511,NULL,'default','Settings for !theme theme','','7.57-dev'),(6512,NULL,'default','Disable !theme theme','','7.57-dev'),(6513,NULL,'default','Set !theme as default theme','','7.57-dev'),(6514,NULL,'default','Enable !theme theme','','7.57-dev'),(6515,NULL,'default','Enable and set default','','7.57-dev'),(6516,NULL,'default','Enable !theme as default theme','','7.57-dev'),(6517,NULL,'default','default theme','','7.57-dev'),(6518,NULL,'default','Choose \"Default theme\" to always use the same theme as the rest of the site.','','7.57-dev'),(6519,NULL,'default','Use the administration theme when editing or creating content','','7.57-dev'),(6520,NULL,'default','The %theme theme has been enabled.','','none'),(6521,NULL,'default','The %theme theme was not found.','','none'),(6522,NULL,'default','%theme is the default theme and cannot be disab