e\".','','none'),(7053,NULL,'default','The selected file %filename cannot be uploaded. Only files with the following extensions are allowed: %extensions.','','none'),(7054,NULL,'default','A flexible, recolorable theme with many regions.','','7.57-dev'),(7055,NULL,'default','Main background','','none'),(7056,NULL,'default','Sidebar background','','none'),(7057,NULL,'default','Sidebar borders','','none'),(7058,NULL,'default','Footer background','','none'),(7059,NULL,'default','Plum','','none'),(7060,NULL,'default','A space-separated list of HTML tags allowed in the content of feed items. Disallowed tags are stripped from the content.','','none'),(7061,NULL,'default','%field may only contain characters a-z, underscores, or hyphens.','','none'),(7062,NULL,'default','%field cannot contain any markup.','','none'),(7063,NULL,'default','No URL aliases available. <a href=\"@link\">Add URL alias</a>.','','none'),(7064,NULL,'default','To provide keyword searching, the search engine maintains an index of words found in the content and its fields, along with text added to your content by other modules (such as comments from the core Comment module, and taxonomy terms from the core Taxonomy module). To build and maintain this index, a correctly configured <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a> is required. Users with <em>Administer search</em> permission can further configure the cron settings on the <a href=\"@searchsettings\">Search settings page</a>.','','7.57-dev'),(7065,NULL,'default','Content reindexing','','7.57-dev'),(7066,NULL,'default','Content-related actions on your site (creating, editing, or deleting content and comments) automatically cause affected content items to be marked for indexing or reindexing at the next cron run. When content is marked for reindexing, the previous content remains in the index until cron runs, at which time it is replaced by the new content. Unlike content-related actions, actions related to the structure of your site do not cause affected content to be marked for reindexing. Examples of structure-related actions that affect content include deleting or editing taxonomy terms, enabling or disabling modules that add text to content (such as Taxonomy, Comment, and field-providing modules), and modifying the fields or display parameters of your content types. If you take one of these actions and you want to ensure that the search index is updated to reflect your changed site structure, you can mark all content for reindexing by clicking the \"Re-index site\" button on the <a href=\"@searchsettings\">Search settings page</a>. If you have a lot of content on your site, it may take several cron runs for the content to be reindexed.','','7.57-dev'),(7067,NULL,'default','These options control the display settings for the %name theme. When your site is displayed using this theme, these settings will be used.','','none'),(7068,NULL,'default','Administer software updates','','7.57-dev'),(7069,NULL,'default','Enter a valid email address or use a token e-mail address such as %author.','','none'),(7070,NULL,'default','@required_name (Missing)','','none'),(7071,NULL,'default','@required_name (Version @compatibility required)','','none'),(7072,NULL,'default','@name requires at least PHP @version.','','none'),(7073,NULL,'default','Unresolved dependency','','none'),(7074,NULL,'default','@name requires this module.','','none'),(7075,NULL,'default','@name requires this module and version. Currently using @required_name version @version','','none'),(7076,NULL,'default','Site details','','none'),(7077,NULL,'default','Title and slogan','','none'),(7078,NULL,'default','Firehouse','','none'),(7079,NULL,'default','Ice','','none'),(7080,NULL,'default','Can\'t handle more than one field storage engine','','none'),(7081,NULL,'default','Field storage engine not found.','','none'),(7082,NULL,'default','For this query an entity type must be specified.','','none'),(7083,NULL,'default','Entity %entity has no base table.','','non